full_text: Underwriting rules are managed in the user interface and contain fields related to define and approve the underwriting issues. Log in as SuperUser. Go to Administration. Select Business Settings, Business Rules, Underwriting Rules. Click Next to view the next page of Underwriting Rules. Clone, an existing underwriting rule to see the underwriting rules. See how the rule is defined. For example, PA, primary driver under 25. Click, Clone. On the Rule Details page, there are several fields that define the underwriting rule. Name identifies the underwriting rule in the user interface. Code must be unique and identifies the underwriting issue type. Select the Checking Set drop-down. Click the Checking Set drop-down. A Checking Set represents a point in a job at which conditions are checked to raise underwriting issues, such as pre-quote, bind or pre-issuance. Click the Blocking Point drop-down. A blocking point stops progress of the job until an issue is approved. In this example, the issue is raised at quote time but it blocks find. Default duration specifies the property on the new approval page and it indicates when an approval will expire. You can enter a description for the rule and a start and end date. In the applies to section, select which policy lines, jurisdictions, and policy transactions this rule applies to. The rule context provides policy data to be used by the rule. You can also create reusable variables. These are the list of predefined context for personal auto policies. This issue uses the context for each vehicle. In the rule conditions section, create the conditions for raising the underwriting issue. In this case, the primary driver's age on a vehicle is less than 25. You can add a new criteria. Click the expression field. The context objects based on the selected rule context can be used to create the left and right expressions. Click the arrow to select a mode for the expression. The list of modes contains formula, count, sum or lookup. There are also several options to choose for the operation. In the underwriting issue details section, the issue key can uniquely identify the underwriting issue once it is raised. The value is compared with authority grants to determine if the user can approve this issue. Short and long description are used to display the underwriting issues on the risk analysis page. Both are localized. Click cancel to go back to the underwriting rules page. The underwriting rule fields related to approval are covered in a separate demonstration. This is the end of demonstration for the underwriting rule fields related to define an issue.
